HEADWORD: Opponency
<hw>Op*po"nen*cy</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <def>The act of
opening an academical disputation; the proposition of objections to a
tenet, as an exercise for a degree.</def> <mark>[Eng.]</mark>
<rj><au>Todd.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

